39bool MakefileGenerator::canExecute(const QStringList &cmdline, int *a) const
40{
41 int argv0 = -1;
42 for(int i = 0; i < cmdline.size(); ++i) {
43 if(!cmdline.at(i).contains(c: '=')) {
44 argv0 = i;
45 break;
46 }
47 }
48 if(a)
49 *a = argv0;
50 if(argv0 != -1) {
51 const QString c = Option::normalizePath(in: cmdline.at(i: argv0));
52 if(exists(file: c))
53 return true;
54 }
55 return false;
56}
57
58QString MakefileGenerator::mkdir_p_asstring(const QString &dir, bool escape) const
59{
60 return "@" + makedir.arg(
61 a: escape ? escapeFilePath(path: Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: dir, fix_env: false, canonical: false)) : dir);
62}
63
64bool MakefileGenerator::mkdir(const QString &in_path) const
65{
66 QString path = Option::normalizePath(in: in_path);
67 if(QFile::exists(fileName: path))
68 return true;
69
70 return QDir().mkpath(dirPath: path);
71}

73void
74MakefileGenerator::verifyCompilers()
75{
76 ProValueMap &v = project->variables();
77 ProStringList &quc = v["QMAKE_EXTRA_COMPILERS"];
78 for(int i = 0; i < quc.size(); ) {
79 bool error = false;
80 const ProString &comp = quc.at(i);
81 const ProKey okey(comp + ".output");
82 if (v[okey].isEmpty()) {
83 const ProKey ofkey(comp + ".output_function");
84 if (!v[ofkey].isEmpty()) {
85 v[okey].append(t: "${QMAKE_FUNC_FILE_IN_" + v[ofkey].first() + "}");
86 } else {
87 error = true;
88 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Compiler: %s: No output file specified", comp.toLatin1().constData());
89 }
90 } else if (v[ProKey(comp + ".input")].isEmpty()) {
91 error = true;
92 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Compiler: %s: No input variable specified", comp.toLatin1().constData());
93 }
94 if(error)
95 quc.removeAt(idx: i);
96 else
97 ++i;
98 }
99}

101void
102MakefileGenerator::initOutPaths()
103{
104 ProValueMap &v = project->variables();
105 //for shadow builds
106 if(!v.contains(key: "QMAKE_ABSOLUTE_SOURCE_PATH")) {
107 if (Option::globals->do_cache && !project->cacheFile().isEmpty() &&
108 v.contains(key: "QMAKE_ABSOLUTE_SOURCE_ROOT")) {
109 QString root = v["QMAKE_ABSOLUTE_SOURCE_ROOT"].first().toQString();
110 root = QDir::fromNativeSeparators(pathName: root);
111 if(!root.isEmpty()) {
112 QFileInfo fi = fileInfo(file: project->cacheFile());
113 if(!fi.makeAbsolute()) {
114 QString cache_r = fi.path(), pwd = Option::output_dir;
115 if(pwd.startsWith(s: cache_r) && !pwd.startsWith(s: root)) {
116 pwd = root + pwd.mid(position: cache_r.size());
117 if(exists(file: pwd))
118 v.insert(key: "QMAKE_ABSOLUTE_SOURCE_PATH", value: ProStringList(pwd));
119 }
120 }
121 }
122 }
123 }
124 if(!v["QMAKE_ABSOLUTE_SOURCE_PATH"].isEmpty()) {
125 ProString &asp = v["QMAKE_ABSOLUTE_SOURCE_PATH"].first();
126 asp = QDir::fromNativeSeparators(pathName: asp.toQString());
127 if(asp.isEmpty() || asp == Option::output_dir) //if they're the same, why bother?
128 v["QMAKE_ABSOLUTE_SOURCE_PATH"].clear();
129 }
130
131 //some builtin directories
132 if(project->isEmpty(v: "PRECOMPILED_DIR") && !project->isEmpty(v: "OBJECTS_DIR"))
133 v["PRECOMPILED_DIR"] = v["OBJECTS_DIR"];
134 static const char * const dirs[] = { "OBJECTS_DIR", "DESTDIR",
135 "SUBLIBS_DIR", "DLLDESTDIR",
136 "PRECOMPILED_DIR", nullptr };
137 for (int x = 0; dirs[x]; x++) {
138 const ProKey dkey(dirs[x]);
139 if (v[dkey].isEmpty())
140 continue;
141 const ProString orig_path = v[dkey].first();
142
143 ProString &pathRef = v[dkey].first();
144 pathRef = fileFixify(file: pathRef.toQString(), fix: FileFixifyFromOutdir);
145
146 if (!pathRef.endsWith(sub: Option::dir_sep))
147 pathRef += Option::dir_sep;
148
149 if (noIO() || (project->first(variableName: "TEMPLATE") == "subdirs"))
150 continue;
151
152 if (inhibitMakeDirOutPath(path: dkey))
153 continue;
154
155 QString path = project->first(variableName: dkey).toQString(); //not to be changed any further
156 path = fileFixify(file: path, fix: FileFixifyBackwards);
157 debug_msg(level: 3, fmt: "Fixed output_dir %s (%s) into %s", dirs[x],
158 orig_path.toLatin1().constData(), path.toLatin1().constData());
159 if(!mkdir(in_path: path))
160 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "%s: Cannot access directory '%s'", dirs[x],
161 path.toLatin1().constData());
162 }
163
164 //out paths from the extra compilers
165 const ProStringList &quc = project->values(v: "QMAKE_EXTRA_COMPILERS");
166 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator it = quc.begin(); it != quc.end(); ++it) {
167 QString tmp_out = project->first(variableName: ProKey(*it + ".output")).toQString();
168 if(tmp_out.isEmpty())
169 continue;
170 const ProStringList &tmp = project->values(v: ProKey(*it + ".input"));
171 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator it2 = tmp.begin(); it2 != tmp.end(); ++it2) {
172 ProStringList &inputs = project->values(v: (*it2).toKey());
173 for (ProStringList::Iterator input = inputs.begin(); input != inputs.end(); ++input) {
174 QString finp = fileFixify(file: (*input).toQString(), fix: FileFixifyFromOutdir);
175 QString path = replaceExtraCompilerVariables(val: tmp_out, in: finp, out: QString(), forShell: NoShell);
176 path = Option::normalizePath(in: path);
177 int slash = path.lastIndexOf(c: '/');
178 if(slash != -1) {
179 path = path.left(n: slash);
180 // Make out path only if it does not contain makefile variables
181 if(!path.contains(s: "${"))
182 if(path != "." &&
183 !mkdir(in_path: fileFixify(file: path, fix: FileFixifyBackwards)))
184 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "%s: Cannot access directory '%s'",
185 (*it).toLatin1().constData(), path.toLatin1().constData());
186 }
187 }
188 }
189 }
190
191 if(!v["DESTDIR"].isEmpty()) {
192 QDir d(v["DESTDIR"].first().toQString());
193 if (Option::normalizePath(in: d.absolutePath()) == Option::normalizePath(in: Option::output_dir))
194 v.remove(key: "DESTDIR");
195 }
196}

198/*
199 * For the given directory path, return true if MakefileGenerator::initOutPaths() should inhibit the
200 * creation of the directory. Overload this in subclasses.
201 */
202bool
203MakefileGenerator::inhibitMakeDirOutPath(const ProKey &path) const
204{
205 Q_UNUSED(path);
206 return false;
207}

216void
217MakefileGenerator::setProjectFile(QMakeProject *p)
218{
219 if(project)
220 return;
221 project = p;
222 if (project->isActiveConfig(config: "win32"))
223 target_mode = TARG_WIN_MODE;
224 else if (project->isActiveConfig(config: "mac"))
225 target_mode = TARG_MAC_MODE;
226 else
227 target_mode = TARG_UNIX_MODE;
228 init();
229 bool linkPrl = (Option::qmake_mode == Option::QMAKE_GENERATE_MAKEFILE)
230 && project->isActiveConfig(config: "link_prl");
231 bool mergeLflags = !project->isActiveConfig(config: "no_smart_library_merge")
232 && !project->isActiveConfig(config: "no_lflags_merge");
233 findLibraries(linkPrl, mergeLflags);
234}

236ProStringList
237MakefileGenerator::findFilesInVPATH(ProStringList l, uchar flags, const QString &vpath_var)
238{
239 ProStringList vpath;
240 const ProValueMap &v = project->variables();
241 for(int val_it = 0; val_it < l.size(); ) {
242 bool remove_file = false;
243 ProString &val = l[val_it];
244 if(!val.isEmpty()) {
245 QString qval = val.toQString();
246 QString file = fixEnvVariables(x: qval);
247 if (file.isEmpty()) {
248 ++val_it;
249 continue;
250 }
251 if(!(flags & VPATH_NoFixify))
252 file = fileFixify(file, fix: FileFixifyBackwards);
253
254 if(exists(file)) {
255 ++val_it;
256 continue;
257 }
258 bool found = false;
259 if (QDir::isRelativePath(path: qval)) {
260 if(vpath.isEmpty()) {
261 if(!vpath_var.isEmpty())
262 vpath = v[ProKey(vpath_var)];
263 vpath += v["VPATH"] + v["QMAKE_ABSOLUTE_SOURCE_PATH"];
264 if(Option::output_dir != qmake_getpwd())
265 vpath << Option::output_dir;
266 }
267 for (ProStringList::Iterator vpath_it = vpath.begin();
268 vpath_it != vpath.end(); ++vpath_it) {
269 QString real_dir = Option::normalizePath(in: (*vpath_it).toQString());
270 if (exists(file: real_dir + '/' + val)) {
271 ProString dir = (*vpath_it);
272 if(!dir.endsWith(sub: Option::dir_sep))
273 dir += Option::dir_sep;
274 val = dir + val;
275 if(!(flags & VPATH_NoFixify))
276 val = fileFixify(file: val.toQString());
277 found = true;
278 debug_msg(level: 1, fmt: "Found file through vpath %s -> %s",
279 file.toLatin1().constData(), val.toLatin1().constData());
280 break;
281 }
282 }
283 }
284 if(!found) {
285 QString dir, regex = val.toQString(), real_dir;
286 if(regex.lastIndexOf(s: Option::dir_sep) != -1) {
287 dir = regex.left(n: regex.lastIndexOf(s: Option::dir_sep) + 1);
288 real_dir = dir;
289 if(!(flags & VPATH_NoFixify))
290 real_dir = fileFixify(file: real_dir, fix: FileFixifyBackwards) + '/';
291 regex.remove(i: 0, len: dir.size());
292 }
293 if(real_dir.isEmpty() || exists(file: real_dir)) {
294 QStringList files = QDir(real_dir).entryList(nameFilters: QStringList(regex),
295 filters: QDir::NoDotAndDotDot | QDir::AllEntries);
296 if(files.isEmpty()) {
297 debug_msg(level: 1, fmt: "%s:%d Failure to find %s in vpath (%s)",
298 __FILE__, __LINE__, val.toLatin1().constData(),
299 vpath.join(sep: QString("::")).toLatin1().constData());
300 if(flags & VPATH_RemoveMissingFiles)
301 remove_file = true;
302 else if(flags & VPATH_WarnMissingFiles)
303 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Failure to find: %s", val.toLatin1().constData());
304 } else {
305 l.removeAt(idx: val_it);
306 QString a;
307 for(int i = (int)files.size()-1; i >= 0; i--) {
308 a = real_dir + files[i];
309 if(!(flags & VPATH_NoFixify))
310 a = fileFixify(file: a);
311 l.insert(i: val_it, t: a);
312 }
313 }
314 } else {
315 debug_msg(level: 1, fmt: "%s:%d Cannot match %s%s, as %s does not exist.",
316 __FILE__, __LINE__, real_dir.toLatin1().constData(),
317 regex.toLatin1().constData(), real_dir.toLatin1().constData());
318 if(flags & VPATH_RemoveMissingFiles)
319 remove_file = true;
320 else if(flags & VPATH_WarnMissingFiles)
321 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Failure to find: %s", val.toLatin1().constData());
322 }
323 }
324 }
325 if(remove_file)
326 l.removeAt(idx: val_it);
327 else
328 ++val_it;
329 }
330 return l;
331}

333void
334MakefileGenerator::initCompiler(const MakefileGenerator::Compiler &comp)
335{
336 ProValueMap &v = project->variables();
337 ProStringList &l = v[ProKey(comp.variable_in)];
338 // find all the relevant file inputs
339 if(!init_compiler_already.contains(key: comp.variable_in)) {
340 init_compiler_already.insert(key: comp.variable_in, value: true);
341 if(!noIO())
342 l = findFilesInVPATH(l, flags: (comp.flags & Compiler::CompilerRemoveNoExist) ?
343 VPATH_RemoveMissingFiles : VPATH_WarnMissingFiles, vpath_var: "VPATH_" + comp.variable_in);
344 }
345}
346
347void
348MakefileGenerator::init()
349{
350 verifyCompilers();
351 initOutPaths();
352
353 ProValueMap &v = project->variables();
354
355 v["QMAKE_BUILTIN_COMPILERS"] = ProStringList() << "C" << "CXX";
356
357 v["QMAKE_LANGUAGE_C"] = ProString("c");
358 v["QMAKE_LANGUAGE_CXX"] = ProString("c++");
359 v["QMAKE_LANGUAGE_OBJC"] = ProString("objective-c");
360 v["QMAKE_LANGUAGE_OBJCXX"] = ProString("objective-c++");
361
362 if (v["TARGET"].isEmpty())
363 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "TARGET is empty");
364
365 makedir = v["QMAKE_MKDIR_CMD"].join(sep: ' ');
366 chkexists = v["QMAKE_CHK_EXISTS"].join(sep: ' ');
367 if (makedir.isEmpty()) { // Backwards compat with Qt < 5.0.2 specs
368 if (isWindowsShell()) {
369 makedir = "if not exist %1 mkdir %1 & if not exist %1 exit 1";
370 chkexists = "if not exist %1";
371 } else {
372 makedir = "test -d %1 || mkdir -p %1";
373 chkexists = "test -e %1 ||";
374 }
375 }
376
377 if (v["QMAKE_CC_O_FLAG"].isEmpty())
378 v["QMAKE_CC_O_FLAG"].append(t: "-o ");
379
380 if (v["QMAKE_LINK_O_FLAG"].isEmpty())
381 v["QMAKE_LINK_O_FLAG"].append(t: "-o ");
382
383 setSystemIncludes(v["QMAKE_DEFAULT_INCDIRS"]);
384
385 ProStringList &incs = project->values(v: "INCLUDEPATH");
386 if (!project->isActiveConfig(config: "no_include_pwd")) {
387 if (Option::output_dir != qmake_getpwd()) {
388 // Pretend that the build dir is the source dir for #include purposes,
389 // consistently with the "transparent shadow builds" strategy. This is
390 // also consistent with #include "foo.h" falling back to #include <foo.h>
391 // behavior if it doesn't find the file in the source dir.
392 incs.prepend(t: Option::output_dir);
393 }
394 // This makes #include <foo.h> work if the header lives in the source dir.
395 // The benefit of that is questionable, as generally the user should use the
396 // correct include style, and extra compilers that put stuff in the source dir
397 // should add the dir themselves.
398 // More importantly, it makes #include "foo.h" work with MSVC when shadow-building,
399 // as this compiler looks files up relative to %CD%, not the source file's parent.
400 incs.prepend(t: qmake_getpwd());
401 }
402 incs.append(t: project->specDir());
403
404 const auto platform = v["QMAKE_PLATFORM"];
405 resolveDependenciesInFrameworks = platform.contains(str: "darwin");
406
407 const char * const cacheKeys[] = { "_QMAKE_STASH_", "_QMAKE_SUPER_CACHE_", nullptr };
408 for (int i = 0; cacheKeys[i]; ++i) {
409 if (v[cacheKeys[i]].isEmpty())
410 continue;
411 const ProString &file = v[cacheKeys[i]].first();
412 if (file.isEmpty())
413 continue;
414
415 QFileInfo fi(fileInfo(file: file.toQString()));
416
417 // If the file lives in the output dir we treat it as 'owned' by
418 // the current project, so it should be distcleaned by it as well.
419 if (fi.path() == Option::output_dir)
420 v["QMAKE_DISTCLEAN"].append(t: fi.fileName());
421 }
422
423 ProStringList &quc = v["QMAKE_EXTRA_COMPILERS"];
424
425 //make sure the COMPILERS are in the correct input/output chain order
426 for(int comp_out = 0, jump_count = 0; comp_out < quc.size(); ++comp_out) {
427 continue_compiler_chain:
428 if(jump_count > quc.size()) //just to avoid an infinite loop here
429 break;
430 const ProKey vokey(quc.at(i: comp_out) + ".variable_out");
431 if (v.contains(key: vokey)) {
432 const ProStringList &outputs = v.value(key: vokey);
433 for(int out = 0; out < outputs.size(); ++out) {
434 for(int comp_in = 0; comp_in < quc.size(); ++comp_in) {
435 if(comp_in == comp_out)
436 continue;
437 const ProKey ikey(quc.at(i: comp_in) + ".input");
438 if (v.contains(key: ikey)) {
439 const ProStringList &inputs = v.value(key: ikey);
440 for(int in = 0; in < inputs.size(); ++in) {
441 if(inputs.at(i: in) == outputs.at(i: out) && comp_out > comp_in) {
442 ++jump_count;
443 //move comp_out to comp_in and continue the compiler chain
444 // quc.move(comp_out, comp_in);
445 quc.insert(i: comp_in, t: quc.value(i: comp_out));
446 // comp_out > comp_in, so the insertion did move everything up
447 quc.remove(i: comp_out + 1);
448 comp_out = comp_in;
449 goto continue_compiler_chain;
450 }
451 }
452 }
453 }
454 }
455 }
456 }
457
458 if(!project->isEmpty(v: "QMAKE_SUBSTITUTES")) {
459 const ProStringList &subs = v["QMAKE_SUBSTITUTES"];
460 for(int i = 0; i < subs.size(); ++i) {
461 QString sub = subs.at(i).toQString();
462 QString inn = sub + ".input", outn = sub + ".output";
463 const ProKey innkey(inn), outnkey(outn);
464 if (v.contains(key: innkey) || v.contains(key: outnkey)) {
465 if (!v.contains(key: innkey) || !v.contains(key: outnkey)) {
466 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Substitute '%s' has only one of .input and .output",
467 sub.toLatin1().constData());
468 continue;
469 }
470 const ProStringList &tinn = v[innkey], &toutn = v[outnkey];
471 if (tinn.size() != 1) {
472 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Substitute '%s.input' does not have exactly one value",
473 sub.toLatin1().constData());
474 continue;
475 }
476 if (toutn.size() != 1) {
477 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Substitute '%s.output' does not have exactly one value",
478 sub.toLatin1().constData());
479 continue;
480 }
481 inn = fileFixify(file: tinn.first().toQString(), fix: FileFixifyToIndir);
482 outn = fileFixify(file: toutn.first().toQString(), fix: FileFixifyBackwards);
483 } else {
484 inn = fileFixify(file: sub, fix: FileFixifyToIndir);
485 if (!QFile::exists(fileName: inn)) {
486 // random insanity for backwards compat: .in file specified with absolute out dir
487 inn = fileFixify(file: sub);
488 }
489 if(!inn.endsWith(s: ".in")) {
490 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Substitute '%s' does not end with '.in'",
491 inn.toLatin1().constData());
492 continue;
493 }
494 outn = fileFixify(file: inn.left(n: inn.size() - 3), fix: FileFixifyBackwards);
495 }
496
497 const ProKey confign(sub + ".CONFIG");
498 bool verbatim = false;
499 if (v.contains(key: confign))
500 verbatim = v[confign].contains(str: QLatin1String("verbatim"));
501
502 QFile in(inn);
503 if (in.open(flags: QFile::ReadOnly)) {
504 QByteArray contentBytes;
505 if (verbatim) {
506 contentBytes = in.readAll();
507 } else {
508 QString contents;
509 QStack<int> state;
510 enum { IN_CONDITION, MET_CONDITION, PENDING_CONDITION };
511 for (int count = 1; !in.atEnd(); ++count) {
512 QString line = QString::fromLatin1(ba: in.readLine());
513 if (line.startsWith(s: "!!IF ")) {
514 if (state.isEmpty() || state.top() == IN_CONDITION) {
515 QString test = line.mid(position: 5, n: line.size()-(5+1));
516 if (project->test(v: test, file: inn, line: count))
517 state.push(t: IN_CONDITION);
518 else
519 state.push(t: PENDING_CONDITION);
520 } else {
521 state.push(t: MET_CONDITION);
522 }
523 } else if (line.startsWith(s: "!!ELIF ")) {
524 if (state.isEmpty()) {
525 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "(%s:%d): Unexpected else condition",
526 in.fileName().toLatin1().constData(), count);
527 } else if (state.top() == PENDING_CONDITION) {
528 QString test = line.mid(position: 7, n: line.size()-(7+1));
529 if (project->test(v: test, file: inn, line: count)) {
530 state.pop();
531 state.push(t: IN_CONDITION);
532 }
533 } else if (state.top() == IN_CONDITION) {
534 state.pop();
535 state.push(t: MET_CONDITION);
536 }
537 } else if (line.startsWith(s: "!!ELSE")) {
538 if (state.isEmpty()) {
539 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "(%s:%d): Unexpected else condition",
540 in.fileName().toLatin1().constData(), count);
541 } else if (state.top() == PENDING_CONDITION) {
542 state.pop();
543 state.push(t: IN_CONDITION);
544 } else if (state.top() == IN_CONDITION) {
545 state.pop();
546 state.push(t: MET_CONDITION);
547 }
548 } else if (line.startsWith(s: "!!ENDIF")) {
549 if (state.isEmpty())
550 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "(%s:%d): Unexpected endif",
551 in.fileName().toLatin1().constData(), count);
552 else
553 state.pop();
554 } else if (state.isEmpty() || state.top() == IN_CONDITION) {
555 contents += project->expand(v: line, file: in.fileName(), line: count);
556 }
557 }
558 contentBytes = contents.toLatin1();
559 }
560 QFile out(outn);
561 QFileInfo outfi(out);
562 if (out.exists() && out.open(flags: QFile::ReadOnly)) {
563 QByteArray old = out.readAll();
564 if (contentBytes == old) {
565 v["QMAKE_INTERNAL_INCLUDED_FILES"].append(t: in.fileName());
566 v["QMAKE_DISTCLEAN"].append(t: outfi.absoluteFilePath());
567 continue;
568 }
569 out.close();
570 if(!out.remove()) {
571 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Cannot clear substitute '%s'",
572 out.fileName().toLatin1().constData());
573 continue;
574 }
575 }
576 mkdir(in_path: outfi.absolutePath());
577 if(out.open(flags: QFile::WriteOnly)) {
578 v["QMAKE_INTERNAL_INCLUDED_FILES"].append(t: in.fileName());
579 v["QMAKE_DISTCLEAN"].append(t: outfi.absoluteFilePath());
580 out.write(data: contentBytes);
581 } else {
582 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Cannot open substitute for output '%s'",
583 out.fileName().toLatin1().constData());
584 }
585 } else {
586 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Cannot open substitute for input '%s'",
587 in.fileName().toLatin1().constData());
588 }
589 }
590 }
591
592 int x;
593
594 //build up a list of compilers
595 QList<Compiler> compilers;
596 {
597 const char *builtins[] = { "OBJECTS", "SOURCES", "PRECOMPILED_HEADER", nullptr };
598 for(x = 0; builtins[x]; ++x) {
599 Compiler compiler;
600 compiler.variable_in = builtins[x];
601 compiler.flags = Compiler::CompilerBuiltin;
602 compiler.type = QMakeSourceFileInfo::TYPE_C;
603 if(!strcmp(s1: builtins[x], s2: "OBJECTS"))
604 compiler.flags |= Compiler::CompilerNoCheckDeps;
605 compilers.append(t: compiler);
606 }
607 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator it = quc.cbegin(); it != quc.cend(); ++it) {
608 const ProStringList &inputs = v[ProKey(*it + ".input")];
609 for(x = 0; x < inputs.size(); ++x) {
610 Compiler compiler;
611 compiler.variable_in = inputs.at(i: x).toQString();
612 compiler.flags = Compiler::CompilerNoFlags;
613 const ProStringList &config = v[ProKey(*it + ".CONFIG")];
614 if (config.indexOf(t: "ignore_no_exist") != -1)
615 compiler.flags |= Compiler::CompilerRemoveNoExist;
616 if (config.indexOf(t: "no_dependencies") != -1)
617 compiler.flags |= Compiler::CompilerNoCheckDeps;
618 if (config.indexOf(t: "add_inputs_as_makefile_deps") != -1)
619 compiler.flags |= Compiler::CompilerAddInputsAsMakefileDeps;
620
621 const ProKey dkey(*it + ".dependency_type");
622 ProString dep_type;
623 if (!project->isEmpty(v: dkey))
624 dep_type = project->first(variableName: dkey);
625 if (dep_type.isEmpty())
626 compiler.type = QMakeSourceFileInfo::TYPE_UNKNOWN;
627 else if(dep_type == "TYPE_UI")
628 compiler.type = QMakeSourceFileInfo::TYPE_UI;
629 else
630 compiler.type = QMakeSourceFileInfo::TYPE_C;
631 compilers.append(t: compiler);
632 }
633 }
634 }
635 { //do the path fixifying
636 ProStringList paths;
637 for(x = 0; x < compilers.size(); ++x) {
638 if(!paths.contains(str: compilers.at(i: x).variable_in))
639 paths << compilers.at(i: x).variable_in;
640 }
641 paths << "INCLUDEPATH" << "QMAKE_INTERNAL_INCLUDED_FILES" << "PRECOMPILED_HEADER";
642 for(int y = 0; y < paths.size(); y++) {
643 ProStringList &l = v[paths[y].toKey()];
644 for (ProStringList::Iterator it = l.begin(); it != l.end(); ++it) {
645 if((*it).isEmpty())
646 continue;
647 QString fn = (*it).toQString();
648 if (exists(file: fn))
649 (*it) = fileFixify(file: fn);
650 }
651 }
652 }
653
654 if(noIO() || !doDepends() || project->isActiveConfig(config: "GNUmake"))
655 QMakeSourceFileInfo::setDependencyMode(QMakeSourceFileInfo::NonRecursive);
656 for(x = 0; x < compilers.size(); ++x)
657 initCompiler(comp: compilers.at(i: x));
658
659 //merge actual compiler outputs into their variable_out. This is done last so that
660 //files are already properly fixified.
661 for (ProStringList::Iterator it = quc.begin(); it != quc.end(); ++it) {
662 const ProKey ikey(*it + ".input");
663 const ProKey vokey(*it + ".variable_out");
664 const ProStringList &config = project->values(v: ProKey(*it + ".CONFIG"));
665 const ProString &tmp_out = project->first(variableName: ProKey(*it + ".output"));
666 if(tmp_out.isEmpty())
667 continue;
668 if (config.indexOf(t: "combine") != -1) {
669 const ProStringList &compilerInputs = project->values(v: ikey);
670 // Don't generate compiler output if it doesn't have input.
671 if (compilerInputs.isEmpty() || project->values(v: compilerInputs.first().toKey()).isEmpty())
672 continue;
673 if(tmp_out.indexOf(s: "$") == -1) {
674 if(!verifyExtraCompiler(c: (*it), f: QString())) //verify
675 continue;
676 QString out = fileFixify(file: tmp_out.toQString(), fix: FileFixifyFromOutdir);
677 bool pre_dep = (config.indexOf(t: "target_predeps") != -1);
678 if (v.contains(key: vokey)) {
679 const ProStringList &var_out = v.value(key: vokey);
680 for(int i = 0; i < var_out.size(); ++i) {
681 ProKey v = var_out.at(i).toKey();
682 if(v == QLatin1String("SOURCES"))
683 v = "GENERATED_SOURCES";
684 else if(v == QLatin1String("OBJECTS"))
685 pre_dep = false;
686 ProStringList &list = project->values(v);
687 if(!list.contains(str: out))
688 list.append(t: out);
689 }
690 } else if (config.indexOf(t: "no_link") == -1) {
691 ProStringList &list = project->values(v: "OBJECTS");
692 pre_dep = false;
693 if(!list.contains(str: out))
694 list.append(t: out);
695 } else {
696 ProStringList &list = project->values(v: "UNUSED_SOURCES");
697 if(!list.contains(str: out))
698 list.append(t: out);
699 }
700 if(pre_dep) {
701 ProStringList &list = project->values(v: "PRE_TARGETDEPS");
702 if(!list.contains(str: out))
703 list.append(t: out);
704 }
705 }
706 } else {
707 const ProStringList &tmp = project->values(v: ikey);
708 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator it2 = tmp.begin(); it2 != tmp.end(); ++it2) {
709 const ProStringList &inputs = project->values(v: (*it2).toKey());
710 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator input = inputs.constBegin(); input != inputs.constEnd(); ++input) {
711 if((*input).isEmpty())
712 continue;
713 QString inpf = (*input).toQString();
714 if (!verifyExtraCompiler(c: (*it).toQString(), f: inpf)) //verify
715 continue;
716 QString out = replaceExtraCompilerVariables(val: tmp_out.toQString(), in: inpf, out: QString(), forShell: NoShell);
717 out = fileFixify(file: out, fix: FileFixifyFromOutdir);
718 bool pre_dep = (config.indexOf(t: "target_predeps") != -1);
719 if (v.contains(key: vokey)) {
720 const ProStringList &var_out = project->values(v: vokey);
721 for(int i = 0; i < var_out.size(); ++i) {
722 ProKey v = var_out.at(i).toKey();
723 if(v == QLatin1String("SOURCES"))
724 v = "GENERATED_SOURCES";
725 else if(v == QLatin1String("OBJECTS"))
726 pre_dep = false;
727 ProStringList &list = project->values(v);
728 if(!list.contains(str: out))
729 list.append(t: out);
730 }
731 } else if (config.indexOf(t: "no_link") == -1) {
732 pre_dep = false;
733 ProStringList &list = project->values(v: "OBJECTS");
734 if(!list.contains(str: out))
735 list.append(t: out);
736 } else {
737 ProStringList &list = project->values(v: "UNUSED_SOURCES");
738 if(!list.contains(str: out))
739 list.append(t: out);
740 }
741 if(pre_dep) {
742 ProStringList &list = project->values(v: "PRE_TARGETDEPS");
743 if(!list.contains(str: out))
744 list.append(t: out);
745 }
746 }
747 }
748 }
749 }
750
751 //handle dependencies
752 depHeuristicsCache.clear();
753 if(!noIO()) {
754 // dependency paths
755 ProStringList incDirs = v["DEPENDPATH"] + v["QMAKE_ABSOLUTE_SOURCE_PATH"];
756 if(project->isActiveConfig(config: "depend_includepath"))
757 incDirs += v["INCLUDEPATH"];
758 QList<QMakeLocalFileName> deplist;
759 deplist.reserve(size: incDirs.size());
760 for (ProStringList::Iterator it = incDirs.begin(); it != incDirs.end(); ++it)
761 deplist.append(t: QMakeLocalFileName((*it).toQString()));
762 QMakeSourceFileInfo::setDependencyPaths(deplist);
763 debug_msg(level: 1, fmt: "Dependency Directories: %s",
764 incDirs.join(sep: QString(" :: ")).toLatin1().constData());
765
766 //add to dependency engine
767 for(x = 0; x < compilers.size(); ++x) {
768 const MakefileGenerator::Compiler &comp = compilers.at(i: x);
769 if(!(comp.flags & Compiler::CompilerNoCheckDeps)) {
770 const ProKey ikey(comp.variable_in);
771 addSourceFiles(v[ikey], seek: QMakeSourceFileInfo::SEEK_DEPS,
772 type: (QMakeSourceFileInfo::SourceFileType)comp.type);
773
774 if (comp.flags & Compiler::CompilerAddInputsAsMakefileDeps) {
775 ProStringList &l = v[ikey];
776 for (int i=0; i < l.size(); ++i) {
777 if(v["QMAKE_INTERNAL_INCLUDED_FILES"].indexOf(t: l.at(i)) == -1)
778 v["QMAKE_INTERNAL_INCLUDED_FILES"].append(t: l.at(i));
779 }
780 }
781 }
782 }
783 }
784
785 processSources(); //remove anything in SOURCES which is included (thus it need not be linked in)
786
787 //all sources and generated sources must be turned into objects at some point (the one builtin compiler)
788 v["OBJECTS"] += createObjectList(sources: v["SOURCES"]) + createObjectList(sources: v["GENERATED_SOURCES"]);
789
790 //Translation files
791 if(!project->isEmpty(v: "TRANSLATIONS")) {
792 ProStringList &trf = project->values(v: "TRANSLATIONS");
793 for (ProStringList::Iterator it = trf.begin(); it != trf.end(); ++it)
794 (*it) = Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: (*it).toQString());
795 }
796
797 //fix up the target deps
798 static const char * const fixpaths[] = { "PRE_TARGETDEPS", "POST_TARGETDEPS", nullptr };
799 for (int path = 0; fixpaths[path]; path++) {
800 ProStringList &l = v[fixpaths[path]];
801 for (ProStringList::Iterator val_it = l.begin(); val_it != l.end(); ++val_it) {
802 if(!(*val_it).isEmpty())
803 (*val_it) = Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: (*val_it).toQString(), fix_env: false, canonical: false);
804 }
805 }
806
807 //extra depends
808 if(!project->isEmpty(v: "DEPENDS")) {
809 ProStringList &l = v["DEPENDS"];
810 for (ProStringList::Iterator it = l.begin(); it != l.end(); ++it) {
811 const ProStringList &files = v[ProKey(*it + ".file")] + v[ProKey(*it + ".files")]; //why do I support such evil things?
812 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator file_it = files.begin(); file_it != files.end(); ++file_it) {
813 QStringList &out_deps = findDependencies(file: (*file_it).toQString());
814 const ProStringList &in_deps = v[ProKey(*it + ".depends")]; //even more evilness..
815 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator dep_it = in_deps.begin(); dep_it != in_deps.end(); ++dep_it) {
816 QString dep = (*dep_it).toQString();
817 if (exists(file: dep)) {
818 out_deps.append(t: dep);
819 } else {
820 QString dir, regex = Option::normalizePath(in: dep);
821 if (regex.lastIndexOf(c: '/') != -1) {
822 dir = regex.left(n: regex.lastIndexOf(c: '/') + 1);
823 regex.remove(i: 0, len: dir.size());
824 }
825 QStringList files = QDir(dir).entryList(nameFilters: QStringList(regex));
826 if(files.isEmpty()) {
827 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Dependency for [%s]: Not found %s", (*file_it).toLatin1().constData(),
828 dep.toLatin1().constData());
829 } else {
830 for(int i = 0; i < files.size(); i++)
831 out_deps.append(t: dir + files[i]);
832 }
833 }
834 }
835 }
836 }
837 }
838
839 // escape qmake command
840 project->values(v: "QMAKE_QMAKE") =
841 ProStringList(escapeFilePath(path: Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: Option::globals->qmake_abslocation, fix_env: false)));
842}
843
844bool
845MakefileGenerator::processPrlFile(QString &file, bool baseOnly)
846{
847 QString f = fileFixify(file, fix: FileFixifyBackwards);
848 // Explicitly given full .prl name
849 if (!baseOnly && f.endsWith(s: Option::prl_ext))
850 return processPrlFileCore(origFile&: file, origName: QStringView(), fixedFile: f);
851 // Explicitly given or derived (from -l) base name
852 if (processPrlFileCore(origFile&: file, origName: QStringView(), fixedFile: f + Option::prl_ext))
853 return true;
854 if (!baseOnly) {
855 // Explicitly given full library name
856 int off = qMax(a: f.lastIndexOf(c: '/'), b: f.lastIndexOf(c: '\\')) + 1;
857 int ext = QStringView(f).mid(pos: off).lastIndexOf(c: '.');
858 if (ext != -1)
859 return processPrlFileBase(origFile&: file, origName: QStringView(f).mid(pos: off), fixedBase: QStringView{f}.left(n: off + ext), slashOff: off);
860 }
861 return false;
862}
863
864bool
865MakefileGenerator::processPrlFileBase(QString &origFile, QStringView origName,
866 QStringView fixedBase, int /*slashOff*/)
867{
868 return processPrlFileCore(origFile, origName, fixedFile: fixedBase + Option::prl_ext);
869}
870
871bool
872MakefileGenerator::processPrlFileCore(QString &origFile, QStringView origName,
873 const QString &fixedFile)
874{
875 const QString meta_file = QMakeMetaInfo::checkLib(lib: fixedFile);
876 if (meta_file.isEmpty())
877 return false;
878 QMakeMetaInfo libinfo;
879 debug_msg(level: 1, fmt: "Processing PRL file: %s", meta_file.toLatin1().constData());
880 if (!libinfo.readLib(meta_file)) {
881 fprintf(stderr, format: "Error processing meta file %s\n", meta_file.toLatin1().constData());
882 return false;
883 }
884 if (project->isActiveConfig(config: "no_read_prl_qmake")) {
885 debug_msg(level: 2, fmt: "Ignored meta file %s", meta_file.toLatin1().constData());
886 return false;
887 }
888 ProString tgt = libinfo.first(v: "QMAKE_PRL_TARGET");
889 if (tgt.isEmpty()) {
890 fprintf(stderr, format: "Error: %s does not define QMAKE_PRL_TARGET\n",
891 meta_file.toLatin1().constData());
892 return false;
893 }
894 if (!tgt.contains(c: '.') && !libinfo.values(v: "QMAKE_PRL_CONFIG").contains(str: "lib_bundle")) {
895 fprintf(stderr, format: "Error: %s defines QMAKE_PRL_TARGET without extension\n",
896 meta_file.toLatin1().constData());
897 return false;
898 }
899 if (origName.isEmpty()) {
900 // We got a .prl file as input, replace it with an actual library.
901 int off = qMax(a: origFile.lastIndexOf(c: '/'), b: origFile.lastIndexOf(c: '\\')) + 1;
902 debug_msg(level: 1, fmt: " Replacing library reference %s with %s",
903 origFile.mid(position: off).toLatin1().constData(),
904 tgt.toQString().toLatin1().constData());
905 origFile.replace(i: off, len: 1000, after: tgt.toQString());
906 } else if (tgt != origName) {
907 // We got an actual library as input, and found the wrong .prl for it.
908 debug_msg(level: 2, fmt: "Mismatched meta file %s (want %s, got %s)",
909 meta_file.toLatin1().constData(),
910 origName.toLatin1().constData(), tgt.toLatin1().constData());
911 return false;
912 }
913 project->values(v: "QMAKE_CURRENT_PRL_LIBS") = libinfo.values(v: "QMAKE_PRL_LIBS");
914 ProStringList &defs = project->values(v: "DEFINES");
915 const ProStringList &prl_defs = project->values(v: "PRL_EXPORT_DEFINES");
916 for (const ProString &def : libinfo.values(v: "QMAKE_PRL_DEFINES"))
917 if (!defs.contains(str: def) && prl_defs.contains(str: def))
918 defs.append(t: def);
919 QString mf = fileFixify(file: meta_file);
920 if (!project->values(v: "QMAKE_PRL_INTERNAL_FILES").contains(str: mf))
921 project->values(v: "QMAKE_PRL_INTERNAL_FILES").append(t: mf);
922 if (!project->values(v: "QMAKE_INTERNAL_INCLUDED_FILES").contains(str: mf))
923 project->values(v: "QMAKE_INTERNAL_INCLUDED_FILES").append(t: mf);
924 return true;
925}

1007bool
1008MakefileGenerator::writeProjectMakefile()
1009{
1010 QTextStream t(&Option::output);
1011
1012 //header
1013 writeHeader(t);
1014
1015 QList<SubTarget*> targets;
1016 {
1017 ProStringList builds = project->values(v: "BUILDS");
1018 targets.reserve(size: builds.size());
1019 for (ProStringList::Iterator it = builds.begin(); it != builds.end(); ++it) {
1020 SubTarget *st = new SubTarget;
1021 targets.append(t: st);
1022 st->makefile = "$(MAKEFILE)." + (*it);
1023 st->name = (*it).toQString();
1024 const ProKey tkey(*it + ".target");
1025 st->target = (project->isEmpty(v: tkey) ? (*it) : project->first(variableName: tkey)).toQString();
1026 }
1027 }
1028 if(project->isActiveConfig(config: "build_all")) {
1029 t << "first: all\n";
1030 QList<SubTarget*>::Iterator it;
1031
1032 //install
1033 t << "install: ";
1034 for (SubTarget *s : std::as_const(t&: targets))
1035 t << s->target << '-';
1036 t << "install " << Qt::endl;
1037
1038 //uninstall
1039 t << "uninstall: ";
1040 for(it = targets.begin(); it != targets.end(); ++it)
1041 t << (*it)->target << "-uninstall ";
1042 t << Qt::endl;
1043 } else {
1044 t << "first: " << targets.first()->target << Qt::endl
1045 << "install: " << targets.first()->target << "-install\n"
1046 << "uninstall: " << targets.first()->target << "-uninstall\n";
1047 }
1048
1049 writeSubTargets(t, subtargets: targets, flags: SubTargetsNoFlags);
1050 if(!project->isActiveConfig(config: "no_autoqmake")) {
1051 QString mkf = escapeDependencyPath(path: fileFixify(file: Option::output.fileName()));
1052 for(QList<SubTarget*>::Iterator it = targets.begin(); it != targets.end(); ++it)
1053 t << escapeDependencyPath(path: (*it)->makefile) << ": " << mkf << Qt::endl;
1054 }
1055 qDeleteAll(c: targets);
1056 return true;
1057}

1063 return false;
1064 writePrlFile();

1067 QTextStream t(&Option::output);

1069#if 1
1070 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Unable to generate output for: %s [TEMPLATE %s]",
1071 Option::output.fileName().toLatin1().constData(),
1072 project->first(variableName: "TEMPLATE").toLatin1().constData());

1074 Option::output.remove();
1075#endif
1076 }
1077 }
1078 return true;
1079}

1092
1093void
1094MakefileGenerator::writePrlFile()
1095{
1096 if((Option::qmake_mode == Option::QMAKE_GENERATE_MAKEFILE ||
1097 Option::qmake_mode == Option::QMAKE_GENERATE_PRL)
1098 && project->values(v: "QMAKE_FAILED_REQUIREMENTS").isEmpty()
1099 && project->isActiveConfig(config: "create_prl")
1100 && (project->first(variableName: "TEMPLATE") == "lib"
1101 || project->first(variableName: "TEMPLATE") == "vclib"
1102 || project->first(variableName: "TEMPLATE") == "aux")
1103 && (!project->isActiveConfig(config: "plugin") || project->isActiveConfig(config: "static"))) { //write prl file
1104 QString local_prl = prlFileName();
1105 QString prl = fileFixify(file: local_prl);
1106 mkdir(in_path: fileInfo(file: local_prl).path());
1107 QFile ft(local_prl);
1108 if(ft.open(flags: QIODevice::WriteOnly)) {
1109 project->values(v: "ALL_DEPS").append(t: prl);
1110 project->values(v: "QMAKE_INTERNAL_PRL_FILE").append(t: prl);
1111 project->values(v: "QMAKE_DISTCLEAN").append(t: prl);
1112 QTextStream t(&ft);
1113 writePrlFile(t);

1118void
1119MakefileGenerator::writeObj(QTextStream &t, const char *src)
1120{
1121 const ProStringList &srcl = project->values(v: src);
1122 const ProStringList objl = createObjectList(sources: srcl);
1123
1124 ProStringList::ConstIterator oit = objl.begin();
1125 ProStringList::ConstIterator sit = srcl.begin();
1126 QLatin1String stringSrc("$src");
1127 QLatin1String stringObj("$obj");
1128 for(;sit != srcl.end() && oit != objl.end(); ++oit, ++sit) {
1129 if((*sit).isEmpty())
1130 continue;
1131
1132 QString srcf = (*sit).toQString();
1133 QString dstf = (*oit).toQString();
1134 t << escapeDependencyPath(path: dstf) << ": " << escapeDependencyPath(path: srcf)
1135 << " " << finalizeDependencyPaths(paths: findDependencies(file: srcf)).join(sep: " \\\n\t\t");
1136
1137 ProKey comp;
1138 for (const ProString &compiler : project->values(v: "QMAKE_BUILTIN_COMPILERS")) {
1139 // Unfortunately we were not consistent about the C++ naming
1140 ProString extensionSuffix = compiler;
1141 if (extensionSuffix == "CXX")
1142 extensionSuffix = ProString("CPP");
1143
1144 // Nor the C naming
1145 ProString compilerSuffix = compiler;
1146 if (compilerSuffix == "C")
1147 compilerSuffix = ProString("CC");
1148
1149 for (const ProString &extension : project->values(v: ProKey("QMAKE_EXT_" + extensionSuffix))) {
1150 if ((*sit).endsWith(sub: extension)) {
1151 comp = ProKey("QMAKE_RUN_" + compilerSuffix);
1152 break;
1153 }
1154 }
1155
1156 if (!comp.isNull())
1157 break;
1158 }
1159
1160 if (comp.isEmpty())
1161 comp = "QMAKE_RUN_CC";
1162 if (!project->isEmpty(v: comp)) {
1163 QString p = var(var: comp);
1164 p.replace(before: stringSrc, after: escapeFilePath(path: srcf));
1165 p.replace(before: stringObj, after: escapeFilePath(path: dstf));
1166 t << "\n\t" << p;
1167 }
1168 t << Qt::endl << Qt::endl;
1169 }

1172QString
1173MakefileGenerator::filePrefixRoot(const QString &root, const QString &path)
1174{
1175 QString ret(path);
1176 if(path.size() > 2 && path[1] == ':') //c:\foo
1177 ret.insert(i: 2, s: root);
1178 else
1179 ret.prepend(s: root);
1180 while (ret.endsWith(c: '\\'))
1181 ret.chop(n: 1);
1182 return ret;

1498ProStringList
1499MakefileGenerator::createObjectList(const ProStringList &sources)
1500{
1501 ProStringList ret;
1502 QString objdir;
1503 if(!project->values(v: "OBJECTS_DIR").isEmpty())
1504 objdir = project->first(variableName: "OBJECTS_DIR").toQString();
1505 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator it = sources.begin(); it != sources.end(); ++it) {
1506 QString sfn = (*it).toQString();
1507 QFileInfo fi(fileInfo(file: Option::normalizePath(in: sfn)));
1508 QString dir;
1509 if (project->isActiveConfig(config: "object_parallel_to_source")) {
1510 // The source paths are relative to the output dir, but we need source-relative paths
1511 QString sourceRelativePath = fileFixify(file: sfn, fix: FileFixifyBackwards);
1512
1513 if (sourceRelativePath.startsWith(s: ".." + Option::dir_sep))
1514 sourceRelativePath = fileFixify(file: sourceRelativePath, fix: FileFixifyAbsolute);
1515
1516 if (QDir::isAbsolutePath(path: sourceRelativePath))
1517 sourceRelativePath.remove(i: 0, len: sourceRelativePath.indexOf(s: Option::dir_sep) + 1);
1518
1519 dir = objdir; // We still respect OBJECTS_DIR
1520
1521 int lastDirSepPosition = sourceRelativePath.lastIndexOf(s: Option::dir_sep);
1522 if (lastDirSepPosition != -1)
1523 dir += QStringView{sourceRelativePath}.left(n: lastDirSepPosition + 1);
1524
1525 if (!noIO()) {
1526 // Ensure that the final output directory of each object exists
1527 QString outRelativePath = fileFixify(file: dir, fix: FileFixifyBackwards);
1528 if (!outRelativePath.isEmpty() && !mkdir(in_path: outRelativePath))
1529 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Cannot create directory '%s'", outRelativePath.toLatin1().constData());
1530 }
1531 } else {
1532 dir = objdir;
1533 }
1534 ret.append(t: dir + fi.completeBaseName() + Option::obj_ext);
1535 }
1536 return ret;
1537}

1539ReplaceExtraCompilerCacheKey::ReplaceExtraCompilerCacheKey(

1541{

1571QString
1572MakefileGenerator::replaceExtraCompilerVariables(
1573 const QString &orig_var, const QStringList &in, const QStringList &out, ReplaceFor forShell)
1574{
1575 //lazy cache
1576 ReplaceExtraCompilerCacheKey cacheKey(orig_var, in, out, forShell);
1577 QString cacheVal = extraCompilerVariablesCache.value(key: cacheKey);
1578 if(!cacheVal.isNull())
1579 return cacheVal;
1580
1581 //do the work
1582 QString ret = orig_var;
1583 QRegularExpression reg_var("\\$\\{.*\\}", QRegularExpression::InvertedGreedinessOption);
1584 QRegularExpressionMatch match;
1585 for (int rep = 0; (match = reg_var.match(subject: ret, offset: rep)).hasMatch(); ) {
1586 rep = match.capturedStart();
1587 QStringList val;
1588 const ProString var(ret.mid(position: rep + 2, n: match.capturedLength() - 3));
1589 bool filePath = false;
1590 if(val.isEmpty() && var.startsWith(sub: QLatin1String("QMAKE_VAR_"))) {
1591 const ProKey varname = var.mid(off: 10).toKey();
1592 val += project->values(v: varname).toQStringList();
1593 }
1594 if(val.isEmpty() && var.startsWith(sub: QLatin1String("QMAKE_VAR_FIRST_"))) {
1595 const ProKey varname = var.mid(off: 16).toKey();
1596 val += project->first(variableName: varname).toQString();
1597 }
1598
1599 if(val.isEmpty() && !in.isEmpty()) {
1600 if(var.startsWith(sub: QLatin1String("QMAKE_FUNC_FILE_IN_"))) {
1601 filePath = true;
1602 const ProKey funcname = var.mid(off: 19).toKey();
1603 val += project->expand(func: funcname, args: QList<ProStringList>() << ProStringList(in));
1604 } else if(var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_BASE") || var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_IN_BASE")) {
1605 filePath = true;
1606 for(int i = 0; i < in.size(); ++i) {
1607 QFileInfo fi(fileInfo(file: Option::normalizePath(in: in.at(i))));
1608 QString base = fi.completeBaseName();
1609 if(base.isNull())
1610 base = fi.fileName();
1611 val += base;
1612 }
1613 } else if (var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_EXT") || var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_IN_EXT")) {
1614 filePath = true;
1615 for(int i = 0; i < in.size(); ++i) {
1616 QFileInfo fi(fileInfo(file: Option::normalizePath(in: in.at(i))));
1617 QString ext;
1618 // Ensure complementarity with QMAKE_FILE_BASE
1619 int baseLen = fi.completeBaseName().size();
1620 if(baseLen == 0)
1621 ext = fi.fileName();
1622 else
1623 ext = fi.fileName().remove(i: 0, len: baseLen);
1624 val += ext;
1625 }
1626 } else if (var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_IN_NAME")) {
1627 filePath = true;
1628 for (int i = 0; i < in.size(); ++i)
1629 val += fileInfo(file: Option::normalizePath(in: in.at(i))).fileName();
1630 } else if(var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_PATH") || var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_IN_PATH")) {
1631 filePath = true;
1632 for(int i = 0; i < in.size(); ++i)
1633 val += fileInfo(file: Option::normalizePath(in: in.at(i))).path();
1634 } else if(var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_NAME") || var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_IN")) {
1635 filePath = true;
1636 for(int i = 0; i < in.size(); ++i)
1637 val += fileInfo(file: Option::normalizePath(in: in.at(i))).filePath();
1638
1639 }
1640 }
1641 if(val.isEmpty() && !out.isEmpty()) {
1642 if(var.startsWith(sub: QLatin1String("QMAKE_FUNC_FILE_OUT_"))) {
1643 filePath = true;
1644 const ProKey funcname = var.mid(off: 20).toKey();
1645 val += project->expand(func: funcname, args: QList<ProStringList>() << ProStringList(out));
1646 } else if (var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_OUT_PATH")) {
1647 filePath = true;
1648 for (int i = 0; i < out.size(); ++i)
1649 val += fileInfo(file: Option::normalizePath(in: out.at(i))).path();
1650 } else if(var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_OUT")) {
1651 filePath = true;
1652 for(int i = 0; i < out.size(); ++i)
1653 val += fileInfo(file: Option::normalizePath(in: out.at(i))).filePath();
1654 } else if(var == QLatin1String("QMAKE_FILE_OUT_BASE")) {
1655 filePath = true;
1656 for(int i = 0; i < out.size(); ++i) {
1657 QFileInfo fi(fileInfo(file: Option::normalizePath(in: out.at(i))));
1658 QString base = fi.completeBaseName();
1659 if(base.isNull())
1660 base = fi.fileName();
1661 val += base;
1662 }
1663 }
1664 }
1665 if(val.isEmpty() && var.startsWith(sub: QLatin1String("QMAKE_FUNC_"))) {
1666 const ProKey funcname = var.mid(off: 11).toKey();
1667 val += project->expand(func: funcname, args: QList<ProStringList>() << ProStringList(in) << ProStringList(out));
1668 }
1669
1670 if(!val.isEmpty()) {
1671 QString fullVal;
1672 if (filePath && forShell != NoShell) {
1673 for(int i = 0; i < val.size(); ++i) {
1674 if(!fullVal.isEmpty())
1675 fullVal += " ";
1676 if (forShell == LocalShell)
1677 fullVal += IoUtils::shellQuote(arg: Option::fixPathToLocalOS(in: val.at(i), fix_env: false));
1678 else
1679 fullVal += escapeFilePath(path: Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: val.at(i), fix_env: false));
1680 }
1681 } else {
1682 fullVal = val.join(sep: ' ');
1683 }
1684 ret.replace(i: match.capturedStart(), len: match.capturedLength(), after: fullVal);
1685 rep += fullVal.size();
1686 } else {
1687 rep = match.capturedEnd();
1688 }
1689 }
1690
1691 //cache the value
1692 extraCompilerVariablesCache.insert(key: cacheKey, value: ret);
1693 return ret;
1694}

1696bool
1697MakefileGenerator::verifyExtraCompiler(const ProString &comp, const QString &file_unfixed)
1698{
1699 if(noIO())
1700 return false;
1701 const QString file = Option::normalizePath(in: file_unfixed);
1702
1703 const ProStringList &config = project->values(v: ProKey(comp + ".CONFIG"));
1704 if (config.indexOf(t: "moc_verify") != -1) {
1705 if(!file.isNull()) {
1706 QMakeSourceFileInfo::addSourceFile(file, seek: QMakeSourceFileInfo::SEEK_MOCS);
1707 if(!mocable(file)) {
1708 return false;
1709 } else {
1710 project->values(v: "MOCABLES").append(t: file);
1711 }
1712 }
1713 } else if (config.indexOf(t: "function_verify") != -1) {
1714 ProString tmp_out = project->first(variableName: ProKey(comp + ".output"));
1715 if(tmp_out.isEmpty())
1716 return false;
1717 ProStringList verify_function = project->values(v: ProKey(comp + ".verify_function"));
1718 if(verify_function.isEmpty())
1719 return false;
1720
1721 for(int i = 0; i < verify_function.size(); ++i) {
1722 bool invert = false;
1723 ProString verify = verify_function.at(i);
1724 if(verify.at(i: 0) == QLatin1Char('!')) {
1725 invert = true;
1726 verify = verify.mid(off: 1);
1727 }
1728
1729 if (config.indexOf(t: "combine") != -1) {
1730 bool pass = project->test(func: verify.toKey(), args: QList<ProStringList>() << ProStringList(tmp_out) << ProStringList(file));
1731 if(invert)
1732 pass = !pass;
1733 if(!pass)
1734 return false;
1735 } else {
1736 const ProStringList &tmp = project->values(v: ProKey(comp + ".input"));
1737 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator it = tmp.begin(); it != tmp.end(); ++it) {
1738 const ProStringList &inputs = project->values(v: (*it).toKey());
1739 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator input = inputs.begin(); input != inputs.end(); ++input) {
1740 if((*input).isEmpty())
1741 continue;
1742 QString inpf = (*input).toQString();
1743 QString in = fileFixify(file: inpf);
1744 if(in == file) {
1745 bool pass = project->test(func: verify.toKey(),
1746 args: QList<ProStringList>() << ProStringList(replaceExtraCompilerVariables(val: tmp_out.toQString(), in: inpf, out: QString(), forShell: NoShell)) <<
1747 ProStringList(file));
1748 if(invert)
1749 pass = !pass;
1750 if(!pass)
1751 return false;
1752 break;
1753 }
1754 }
1755 }
1756 }
1757 }
1758 } else if (config.indexOf(t: "verify") != -1) {
1759 QString tmp_out = project->first(variableName: ProKey(comp + ".output")).toQString();
1760 if(tmp_out.isEmpty())
1761 return false;
1762 const QString tmp_cmd = project->values(v: ProKey(comp + ".commands")).join(sep: ' ');
1763 if (config.indexOf(t: "combine") != -1) {
1764 QString cmd = replaceExtraCompilerVariables(val: tmp_cmd, in: QString(), out: tmp_out, forShell: LocalShell);
1765 if(system(command: cmd.toLatin1().constData()))
1766 return false;
1767 } else {
1768 const ProStringList &tmp = project->values(v: ProKey(comp + ".input"));
1769 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator it = tmp.begin(); it != tmp.end(); ++it) {
1770 const ProStringList &inputs = project->values(v: (*it).toKey());
1771 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator input = inputs.begin(); input != inputs.end(); ++input) {
1772 if((*input).isEmpty())
1773 continue;
1774 QString inpf = (*input).toQString();
1775 QString in = fileFixify(file: inpf);
1776 if(in == file) {
1777 QString out = replaceExtraCompilerVariables(val: tmp_out, in: inpf, out: QString(), forShell: NoShell);
1778 QString cmd = replaceExtraCompilerVariables(val: tmp_cmd, in, out, forShell: LocalShell);
1779 if(system(command: cmd.toLatin1().constData()))
1780 return false;
1781 break;
1782 }
1783 }
1784 }
1785 }
1786 }
1787 return true;
1788}

1817
1818static QStringList splitDeps(const QString &indeps, bool lineMode)
1819{
1820 if (!lineMode)
1821 return indeps.simplified().split(sep: ' ');
1822 QStringList deps = indeps.split(sep: '\n', behavior: Qt::SkipEmptyParts);
1823#ifdef Q_OS_WIN
1824 for (auto &dep : deps) {
1825 if (dep.endsWith(QLatin1Char('\r')))
1826 dep.chop(1);
1827 }
1828#endif
1829 return deps;

1831
1832QString MakefileGenerator::resolveDependency(const QDir &outDir, const QString &file)
1833{
1834 const QList<QMakeLocalFileName> &depdirs = QMakeSourceFileInfo::dependencyPaths();
1835 for (const auto &depdir : depdirs) {
1836 const QString &local = depdir.local();
1837 QString lf = outDir.absoluteFilePath(fileName: local + '/' + file);
1838 if (exists(file: lf))
1839 return lf;
1840
1841 if (resolveDependenciesInFrameworks) {
1842 // Given a file like "QtWidgets/QWidget", try to resolve it
1843 // as framework header "QtWidgets.framework/Headers/QWidget".
1844 int cut = file.indexOf(c: '/');
1845 if (cut < 0 || cut + 1 >= file.size())
1846 continue;
1847 QStringView framework = QStringView{file}.left(n: cut);
1848 QStringView include = QStringView(file).mid(pos: cut + 1);
1849 if (local.endsWith(s: '/' + framework + ".framework/Headers")) {
1850 lf = outDir.absoluteFilePath(fileName: local + '/' + include);
1851 if (exists(file: lf))
1852 return lf;
1853 }
1854 }
1855 }
1856 return {};
1857}
1858
1859void MakefileGenerator::callExtraCompilerDependCommand(const ProString &extraCompiler,
1860 const QString &tmp_dep_cmd,
1861 const QString &inpf,
1862 const QString &tmp_out,
1863 bool dep_lines,
1864 QStringList *deps,
1865 bool existingDepsOnly,
1866 bool checkCommandAvailability)
1867{
1868 char buff[256];
1869 QString dep_cmd = replaceExtraCompilerVariables(val: tmp_dep_cmd, in: inpf, out: tmp_out, forShell: LocalShell);
1870 if (checkCommandAvailability && !canExecute(cmdline: dep_cmd))
1871 return;
1872 dep_cmd = QLatin1String("cd ")
1873 + IoUtils::shellQuote(arg: Option::fixPathToLocalOS(in: Option::output_dir, fix_env: false))
1874 + QLatin1String(" && ")
1875 + fixEnvVariables(x: dep_cmd);
1876 if (FILE *proc = QT_POPEN(command: dep_cmd.toLatin1().constData(), QT_POPEN_READ)) {
1877 QByteArray depData;
1878 while (int read_in = feof(stream: proc) ? 0 : (int)fread(ptr: buff, size: 1, n: 255, stream: proc))
1879 depData.append(s: buff, len: read_in);
1880 QT_PCLOSE(stream: proc);
1881 const QString indeps = QString::fromLocal8Bit(ba: depData);
1882 if (indeps.isEmpty())
1883 return;
1884 QDir outDir(Option::output_dir);
1885 QStringList dep_cmd_deps = splitDeps(indeps, lineMode: dep_lines);
1886 for (int i = 0; i < dep_cmd_deps.size(); ++i) {
1887 QString &file = dep_cmd_deps[i];
1888 const QString absFile = outDir.absoluteFilePath(fileName: file);
1889 if (absFile == file) {
1890 // already absolute; don't do any checks.
1891 } else if (exists(file: absFile)) {
1892 file = absFile;
1893 } else {
1894 const QString localFile = resolveDependency(outDir, file);
1895 if (localFile.isEmpty()) {
1896 if (exists(file)) {
1897 warn_msg(t: WarnDeprecated, fmt: ".depend_command for extra compiler %s"
1898 " prints paths relative to source directory",
1899 extraCompiler.toLatin1().constData());
1900 } else if (existingDepsOnly) {
1901 file.clear();
1902 } else {
1903 file = absFile; // fallback for generated resources
1904 }
1905 } else {
1906 file = localFile;
1907 }
1908 }
1909 if (!file.isEmpty())
1910 file = fileFixify(file);
1911 }
1912 deps->append(l: dep_cmd_deps);
1913 }
1914}

2147void

2151 const ProStringList &quc = project->values(v: "QMAKE_EXTRA_COMPILERS");

2315QList<MakefileGenerator::SubTarget*>
2316MakefileGenerator::findSubDirsSubTargets() const
2317{
2318 QList<SubTarget*> targets;
2319 {
2320 const ProStringList &subdirs = project->values(v: "SUBDIRS");
2321 for(int subdir = 0; subdir < subdirs.size(); ++subdir) {
2322 ProString ofile = subdirs[subdir];
2323 QString oname = ofile.toQString();
2324 QString fixedSubdir = oname;
2325 fixedSubdir.replace(re: QRegularExpression("[^a-zA-Z0-9_]"),after: "-");
2326
2327 SubTarget *st = new SubTarget;
2328 st->name = oname;
2329 targets.append(t: st);
2330
2331 bool fromFile = false;
2332 const ProKey fkey(fixedSubdir + ".file");
2333 const ProKey skey(fixedSubdir + ".subdir");
2334 if (!project->isEmpty(v: fkey)) {
2335 if (!project->isEmpty(v: skey))
2336 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Cannot assign both file and subdir for subdir %s",
2337 subdirs[subdir].toLatin1().constData());
2338 ofile = project->first(variableName: fkey);
2339 fromFile = true;
2340 } else if (!project->isEmpty(v: skey)) {
2341 ofile = project->first(variableName: skey);
2342 fromFile = false;
2343 } else {
2344 fromFile = ofile.endsWith(sub: Option::pro_ext);
2345 }
2346 QString file = Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: ofile.toQString());
2347
2348 if(fromFile) {
2349 int slsh = file.lastIndexOf(s: Option::dir_sep);
2350 if(slsh != -1) {
2351 st->in_directory = file.left(n: slsh+1);
2352 st->profile = file.mid(position: slsh+1);
2353 } else {
2354 st->profile = file;
2355 }
2356 } else {
2357 if (!file.isEmpty() && !project->isActiveConfig(config: "subdir_first_pro")) {
2358 const QString baseName = file.section(in_sep: Option::dir_sep, start: -1);
2359 if (baseName.isEmpty()) {
2360 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Ignoring invalid SUBDIRS entry %s",
2361 subdirs[subdir].toLatin1().constData());
2362 continue;
2363 }
2364 st->profile = baseName + Option::pro_ext;
2365 }
2366 st->in_directory = file;
2367 }
2368 while(st->in_directory.endsWith(s: Option::dir_sep))
2369 st->in_directory.chop(n: 1);
2370 if(fileInfo(file: st->in_directory).isRelative())
2371 st->out_directory = st->in_directory;
2372 else
2373 st->out_directory = fileFixify(file: st->in_directory, fix: FileFixifyBackwards);
2374 const ProKey mkey(fixedSubdir + ".makefile");
2375 if (!project->isEmpty(v: mkey)) {
2376 st->makefile = project->first(variableName: mkey).toQString();
2377 } else {
2378 st->makefile = "Makefile";
2379 if(!st->profile.isEmpty()) {
2380 QString basename = st->in_directory;
2381 int new_slsh = basename.lastIndexOf(s: Option::dir_sep);
2382 if(new_slsh != -1)
2383 basename = basename.mid(position: new_slsh+1);
2384 if(st->profile != basename + Option::pro_ext)
2385 st->makefile += "." + st->profile.left(n: st->profile.size() - Option::pro_ext.size());
2386 }
2387 }
2388 const ProKey dkey(fixedSubdir + ".depends");
2389 if (!project->isEmpty(v: dkey)) {
2390 const ProStringList &depends = project->values(v: dkey);
2391 for(int depend = 0; depend < depends.size(); ++depend) {
2392 bool found = false;
2393 for(int subDep = 0; subDep < subdirs.size(); ++subDep) {
2394 if(subdirs[subDep] == depends.at(i: depend)) {
2395 QString subName = subdirs[subDep].toQString();
2396 QString fixedSubDep = subName;
2397 fixedSubDep.replace(re: QRegularExpression("[^a-zA-Z0-9_]"),after: "-");
2398 const ProKey dtkey(fixedSubDep + ".target");
2399 if (!project->isEmpty(v: dtkey)) {
2400 st->depends += project->first(variableName: dtkey);
2401 } else {
2402 QString d = Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: subName);
2403 const ProKey dfkey(fixedSubDep + ".file");
2404 if (!project->isEmpty(v: dfkey)) {
2405 d = project->first(variableName: dfkey).toQString();
2406 } else {
2407 const ProKey dskey(fixedSubDep + ".subdir");
2408 if (!project->isEmpty(v: dskey))
2409 d = project->first(variableName: dskey).toQString();
2410 }
2411 st->depends += "sub-" + d.replace(re: QRegularExpression("[^a-zA-Z0-9_]"),after: "-");
2412 }
2413 found = true;
2414 break;
2415 }
2416 }
2417 if(!found) {
2418 QString depend_str = depends.at(i: depend).toQString();
2419 st->depends += depend_str.replace(re: QRegularExpression("[^a-zA-Z0-9_]"),after: "-");
2420 }
2421 }
2422 }
2423 const ProKey tkey(fixedSubdir + ".target");
2424 if (!project->isEmpty(v: tkey)) {
2425 st->target = project->first(variableName: tkey).toQString();
2426 } else {
2427 st->target = "sub-" + file;
2428 st->target.replace(re: QRegularExpression("[^a-zA-Z0-9_]"), after: "-");
2429 }
2430 }
2431 }
2432 return targets;
2433}

2679 if(dep.isEmpty())
2680 dep = (*dep_it).toQString();
2681 deps += ' ' + escapeDependencyPath(path: Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: dep, fix_env: false));
2682 }
2683 if (config.indexOf(t: "recursive") != -1) {
2684 QSet<QString> recurse;
2685 const ProKey rkey(*qut_it + ".recurse");
2686 if (project->isSet(v: rkey)) {
2687 const QStringList values = project->values(v: rkey).toQStringList();
2688 recurse = QSet<QString>(values.begin(), values.end());
2689 } else {
2690 for(int target = 0; target < targets.size(); ++target)
2691 recurse.insert(value: targets.at(i: target)->name);
2692 }
2693 for(int target = 0; target < targets.size(); ++target) {
2694 SubTarget *subtarget = targets.at(i: target);
2695 QString in_directory = subtarget->in_directory;
2696 if(!in_directory.isEmpty() && !in_directory.endsWith(s: Option::dir_sep))
2697 in_directory += Option::dir_sep;
2698 QString out_directory = subtarget->out_directory;
2699 if(!out_directory.isEmpty() && !out_directory.endsWith(s: Option::dir_sep))
2700 out_directory += Option::dir_sep;
2701 if(!abs_source_path.isEmpty() && out_directory.startsWith(s: abs_source_path))
2702 out_directory = Option::output_dir + out_directory.mid(position: abs_source_path.size());
2703
2704 if(!recurse.contains(value: subtarget->name))
2705 continue;
2706
2707 QString out_directory_cdin = out_directory.isEmpty() ? QString("\n\t")
2708 : "\n\tcd " + escapeFilePath(path: out_directory) + " && ";
2709 QString makefilein = " -f " + escapeFilePath(path: subtarget->makefile);
2710
2711 QString out;
2712 QString in;
2713 if (!subtarget->profile.isEmpty()) {
2714 out = subtarget->makefile;
2715 in = escapeFilePath(path: fileFixify(file: in_directory + subtarget->profile, fix: FileFixifyAbsolute));
2716 if (out.startsWith(s: in_directory))
2717 out = out.mid(position: in_directory.size());
2718 out = escapeFilePath(path: out);
2719 }
2720
2721 //write the rule/depends
2722 if(flags & SubTargetOrdered) {
2723 const QString dep = subtarget->target + "-" + (*qut_it) + "_ordered";
2724 t << dep << ":";
2725 if(target)
2726 t << " " << targets.at(i: target-1)->target << "-" << (*qut_it) << "_ordered ";
2727 deps += " " + dep;
2728 } else {
2729 const QString dep = subtarget->target + "-" + (*qut_it);
2730 t << dep << ":";
2731 if(!subtarget->depends.isEmpty())
2732 t << " " << valGlue(varList: subtarget->depends, before: QString(), glue: "-" + (*qut_it) + " ", after: "-" + (*qut_it));
2733 deps += " " + dep;
2734 }
2735
2736 QString sub_targ = targ;
2737 const ProKey rtkey(*qut_it + ".recurse_target");
2738 if (project->isSet(v: rtkey))
2739 sub_targ = project->first(variableName: rtkey).toQString();
2740
2741 //write the commands
2742 writeSubTargetCall(t, in_directory, in, out_directory, out,
2743 out_directory_cdin, makefilein: makefilein + " " + sub_targ);
2744 }
2745 }
2746 if (config.indexOf(t: "phony") != -1)
2747 deps += " FORCE";
2748 t << escapeDependencyPath(path: Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: targ, fix_env: false)) << ":" << deps << "\n";
2749 if(!cmd.isEmpty())
2750 t << "\t" << cmd << Qt::endl;
2751 }
2752
2753 if(flags & SubTargetInstalls) {
2754 project->values(v: "INSTALLDEPS") += "install_subtargets";
2755 project->values(v: "UNINSTALLDEPS") += "uninstall_subtargets";
2756 writeInstalls(t, noBuild: true);
2757 }
2758 t << "FORCE:\n\n";
2759 suppressBuiltinRules(t);

2891QString
2892MakefileGenerator::escapeDependencyPath(const QString &path) const
2893{
2894 QString ret = path;
2895 if (!ret.isEmpty()) {
2896 // Unix make semantics, to be inherited by unix and mingw generators.
2897#ifdef Q_OS_UNIX
2898 // When running on Unix, we need to escape colons (which may appear
2899 // anywhere in a path, and would be mis-parsed as dependency separators).
2900 static const QRegularExpression criticalChars(QStringLiteral("([\t :#])"));
2901#else
2902 // MinGW make has a hack for colons which denote drive letters, and no
2903 // other colons may appear in paths. And escaping colons actually breaks
2904 // the make from the Android SDK.
2905 static const QRegularExpression criticalChars(QStringLiteral("([\t #])"));
2906#endif
2907 ret.replace(re: criticalChars, QStringLiteral("\\\\1"));
2908 ret.replace(c: QLatin1Char('='), QStringLiteral("$(EQ)"));
2909 debug_msg(level: 2, fmt: "escapeDependencyPath: %s -> %s", path.toLatin1().constData(), ret.toLatin1().constData());
2910 }
2911 return ret;
2912}

2966QString
2967MakefileGenerator::fileFixify(const QString &file, FileFixifyTypes fix, bool canon) const
2968{
2969 if(file.isEmpty())
2970 return file;
2971 QString ret = file;
2972
2973 //do the fixin'
2974 QString orig_file = ret;
2975 if(ret.startsWith(c: QLatin1Char('~'))) {
2976 if(ret.startsWith(s: QLatin1String("~/")))
2977 ret = QDir::homePath() + ret.mid(position: 1);
2978 else
2979 warn_msg(t: WarnLogic, fmt: "Unable to expand ~ in %s", ret.toLatin1().constData());
2980 }
2981 if ((fix & FileFixifyAbsolute)
2982 || (!(fix & FileFixifyRelative) && project->isActiveConfig(config: "no_fixpath"))) {
2983 if ((fix & FileFixifyAbsolute) && QDir::isRelativePath(path: ret)) {
2984 QString pwd = !(fix & FileFixifyFromOutdir) ? project->projectDir() : Option::output_dir;
2985 {
2986 QFileInfo in_fi(fileInfo(file: pwd));
2987 if (in_fi.exists())
2988 pwd = in_fi.canonicalFilePath();
2989 }
2990 if (!pwd.endsWith(c: QLatin1Char('/')))
2991 pwd += QLatin1Char('/');
2992 ret.prepend(s: pwd);
2993 }
2994 ret = Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: ret, fix_env: false, canonical: canon);
2995 } else { //fix it..
2996 QString out_dir = (fix & FileFixifyToIndir) ? project->projectDir() : Option::output_dir;
2997 QString in_dir = !(fix & FileFixifyFromOutdir) ? project->projectDir() : Option::output_dir;
2998 {
2999 QFileInfo in_fi(fileInfo(file: in_dir));
3000 if(in_fi.exists())
3001 in_dir = in_fi.canonicalFilePath();
3002 QFileInfo out_fi(fileInfo(file: out_dir));
3003 if(out_fi.exists())
3004 out_dir = out_fi.canonicalFilePath();
3005 }
3006
3007 QString qfile(Option::normalizePath(in: ret));
3008 QFileInfo qfileinfo(fileInfo(file: qfile));
3009 if(out_dir != in_dir || !qfileinfo.isRelative()) {
3010 if(qfileinfo.isRelative()) {
3011 ret = in_dir + "/" + qfile;
3012 qfileinfo.setFile(ret);
3013 }
3014 ret = Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: ret, fix_env: false, canonical: canon);
3015 QString match_dir = Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: out_dir, fix_env: false, canonical: canon);
3016 if(ret == match_dir) {
3017 ret = "";
3018 } else if(ret.startsWith(s: match_dir + Option::dir_sep)) {
3019 ret = ret.mid(position: match_dir.size() + Option::dir_sep.size());
3020 } else {
3021 //figure out the depth
3022 int depth = 4;
3023 if(Option::qmake_mode == Option::QMAKE_GENERATE_MAKEFILE ||
3024 Option::qmake_mode == Option::QMAKE_GENERATE_PRL) {
3025 if(project && !project->isEmpty(v: "QMAKE_PROJECT_DEPTH"))
3026 depth = project->first(variableName: "QMAKE_PROJECT_DEPTH").toInt();
3027 else if(Option::mkfile::cachefile_depth != -1)
3028 depth = Option::mkfile::cachefile_depth;
3029 }
3030 //calculate how much can be removed
3031 QString dot_prefix;
3032 for(int i = 1; i <= depth; i++) {
3033 int sl = match_dir.lastIndexOf(s: Option::dir_sep);
3034 if(sl == -1)
3035 break;
3036 match_dir = match_dir.left(n: sl);
3037 if(match_dir.isEmpty())
3038 break;
3039 if(ret.startsWith(s: match_dir + Option::dir_sep)) {
3040 //concat
3041 int remlen = ret.size() - (match_dir.size() + 1);
3042 if(remlen < 0)
3043 remlen = 0;
3044 ret = ret.right(n: remlen);
3045 //prepend
3046 for(int o = 0; o < i; o++)
3047 dot_prefix += ".." + Option::dir_sep;
3048 break;
3049 }
3050 }
3051 ret.prepend(s: dot_prefix);
3052 }
3053 } else {
3054 ret = Option::fixPathToTargetOS(in: ret, fix_env: false, canonical: canon);
3055 }
3056 }
3057 if(ret.isEmpty())
3058 ret = ".";
3059 debug_msg(level: 3, fmt: "Fixed[%d,%d] %s :: to :: %s [%s::%s]",
3060 int(fix), canon, orig_file.toLatin1().constData(), ret.toLatin1().constData(),
3061 qmake_getpwd().toLatin1().constData(), Option::output_dir.toLatin1().constData());
3062 return ret;
3063}

3236 ret = ret.right(n: ret.size() - slsh - 1);
3237 if (ret.startsWith(s: "lib"))
3238 ret = ret.mid(position: 3);
3239 int dot = ret.indexOf(c: '.');
3240 if (dot != -1)
3241 ret = ret.left(n: dot);
3242 }
3243 ret += Option::pkgcfg_ext;
3244 QString subdir = project->first(variableName: "QMAKE_PKGCONFIG_DESTDIR").toQString();
3245 if(!subdir.isEmpty()) {
3246 // initOutPaths() appends dir_sep, but just to be safe..
3247 if (!subdir.endsWith(s: Option::dir_sep))
3248 ret.prepend(s: Option::dir_sep);
3249 ret.prepend(s: subdir);
3250 }
3251 if(fixify) {
3252 if(QDir::isRelativePath(path: ret) && !project->isEmpty(v: "DESTDIR"))
3253 ret.prepend(s: project->first(variableName: "DESTDIR").toQString());
3254 ret = fileFixify(file: ret, fix: FileFixifyBackwards);
3255 }
3256 return ret;
3257}

3423static QString windowsifyPath(const QString &str)
3424{
3425 // The paths are escaped in prl files, so every slash needs to turn into two backslashes.
3426 // Then each backslash needs to be escaped for sed. And another level for C quoting here.
3427 return QString(str).replace(c: '/', after: QLatin1String("\\\\\\\\"));
3428}
3429
3430QString MakefileGenerator::createSedArgs(const ProKey &replace_rule, const QString &file_name) const
3431{
3432 QString sedargs;
3433 if (!project->isEmpty(v: replace_rule) && !project->isActiveConfig(config: "no_sed_meta_install")) {
3434 const ProStringList &replace_rules = project->values(v: replace_rule);
3435 for (int r = 0; r < replace_rules.size(); ++r) {
3436 const ProString match = project->first(variableName: ProKey(replace_rules.at(i: r) + ".match")),
3437 replace = project->first(variableName: ProKey(replace_rules.at(i: r) + ".replace")),
3438 filename = project->first(variableName: ProKey(replace_rules.at(i: r) + ".filename"));
3439 if (!match.isEmpty() /*&& match != replace*/
3440 && (filename.isEmpty() || filename == file_name)) {
3441 sedargs += " -e " + shellQuote(str: "s," + match + "," + replace + ",g");
3442 if (isWindowsShell()
3443 && project->first(variableName: ProKey(replace_rules.at(i: r) + ".CONFIG")).contains(s: "path"))
3444 sedargs += " -e "
3445 + shellQuote(str: "s," + windowsifyPath(str: match.toQString()) + ","
3446 + windowsifyPath(str: replace.toQString()) + ",gi");
3447 }
3448 }
3449 }
3450 return sedargs;
3451}
3452
3453QString MakefileGenerator::installMetaFile(const ProKey &replace_rule, const QString &src,
3454 const QString &dst) const
3455{
3456 QString ret;
3457 QString sedargs = createSedArgs(replace_rule);
3458 if (sedargs.isEmpty()) {
3459 ret = "$(INSTALL_FILE) " + escapeFilePath(path: src) + ' ' + escapeFilePath(path: dst);
3460 } else {
3461 ret = "$(SED) " + sedargs + ' ' + escapeFilePath(path: src) + " > " + escapeFilePath(path: dst);
3462 }
3463 return ret;
3464}

3480/*
3481 * Create a response file and return its file name.
3482 */
3483QString MakefileGenerator::createResponseFile(
3484 const QString &baseName,
3485 const ProStringList &objList,
3486 const QString &prefix) const
3487{
3488 QString fileName = baseName + '.' + var(var: "QMAKE_ORIG_TARGET");
3489 if (!var(var: "BUILD_NAME").isEmpty())
3490 fileName += '.' + var(var: "BUILD_NAME");
3491 if (!var(var: "MAKEFILE").isEmpty())
3492 fileName += '.' + var(var: "MAKEFILE");
3493 QString filePath = Option::output_dir + QDir::separator() + fileName;
3494 QFile file(filePath);
3495 if (!file.open(flags: QIODevice::WriteOnly | QIODevice::Text)) {
3496 fprintf(stderr, format: "Error: Cannot open response file '%s' for writing.\n",
3497 qPrintable(filePath));
3498 exit(status: 1);
3499 }
3500 QTextStream t(&file);
3501 for (ProStringList::ConstIterator it = objList.constBegin(); it != objList.constEnd(); ++it) {
3502 QString path = (*it).toQString();
3503 // In response files, whitespace and special characters are
3504 // escaped with a backslash; backslashes themselves can either
3505 // be escaped into double backslashes, or, as this is a list of
3506 // path names, converted to forward slashes.
3507 path.replace(c: QLatin1Char('\\'), after: QLatin1String("/"))
3508 .replace(c: QLatin1Char(' '), after: QLatin1String("\\ "))
3509 .replace(c: QLatin1Char('\t'), after: QLatin1String("\\\t"))
3510 .replace(c: QLatin1Char('"'), after: QLatin1String("\\\""))
3511 .replace(c: QLatin1Char('\''), after: QLatin1String("\\'"));
3512 t << prefix << path << Qt::endl;
3513 }
3514 t.flush();
3515 file.close();
3516 return fileName;
3517}

3519/*
3520 * If the threshold for response files are overstepped, create a response file for the linker
3521 * command line.
3522 */
3523MakefileGenerator::LinkerResponseFileInfo MakefileGenerator::maybeCreateLinkerResponseFile() const
3524{
3525 bool useLinkObjectMax = false;
3526 bool ok;
3527 int threshold = project->first(variableName: "QMAKE_RESPONSEFILE_THRESHOLD").toInt(ok: &ok);
3528 if (!ok) {
3529 threshold = project->first(variableName: "QMAKE_LINK_OBJECT_MAX").toInt(ok: &ok);
3530 if (ok)
3531 useLinkObjectMax = true;
3532 }
3533 if (!ok)
3534 return {};
3535
3536 ProStringList linkerInputs = project->values(v: "OBJECTS");
3537 if (useLinkObjectMax) {
3538 // When using QMAKE_LINK_OBJECT_MAX, the number of object files (regardless of their path
3539 // length) decides whether to use a response file. This is far from being a useful
3540 // heuristic but let's keep this behavior for backwards compatibility.
3541 if (linkerInputs.size() < threshold)
3542 return {};
3543 } else {
3544 // When using QMAKE_REPONSEFILE_THRESHOLD, try to determine the command line length of the
3545 // inputs.
3546 linkerInputs += project->values(v: "LIBS");
3547 int totalLength = std::accumulate(first: linkerInputs.cbegin(), last: linkerInputs.cend(), init: 0,
3548 binary_op: [](int total, const ProString &input) {
3549 return total + input.size() + 1;
3550 });
3551 if (totalLength < threshold)
3552 return {};
3553 }
3554
3555 return {
3556 .filePath: createResponseFile(baseName: fileVar(var: "OBJECTS_DIR") + var(var: "QMAKE_LINK_OBJECT_SCRIPT"), objList: linkerInputs),
3557 .onlyObjects: useLinkObjectMax
3558 };
3559}
